Description: Chandler Telecaster. Condition is Used.There are a couple of very small nick's and scratches, but they are very minimal for a nearly thirty year old guitar and won't show up in the pictures. One-of-a-kind Custom 1990s build with Chandler USA and ESP Japan parts. The neck is an early Chandler USA neck hand made in their old San Francisco shop. The figured ash body is master built per special order from the ESP custom shop in Tokyo (luthier date 1989). Original Chandler bodies were made by ESP in Japan. I bought this with intention of keeping it stock but the guitar had dual 500k pots and I didn't find the tone of the guitar to match it's beauty. I then proceeded to take things to the next level. I took a look under the pickguard and realized that I had some options to play with. I installed TV Jones pickups, T-Armond in the neck and a Starwood in the bridge. I then wired it to 500k/250k concentric knobs. The neck pick uses 500k volume and tone. The bridge pickup uses 250k volume and tone. It has a raw Bakelite pickguard and titanium saddles. The neck is a thin U shape that is very fast and easy to play on. Plays and sounds fantastic with amazing build quality. Ships in a roadworn ESP hardshell case. You'll get exactly what you see. Please take a look at my seller feedback. I am only selling to offset this year's tax burden. I really wish I didn't have to. *Price temporarily lowrred to facilitate a quick sale*
Title: Chandler Telecaster
